But Mortimer finds pledges that, before the feast of St. Hilary, he will make his peace, or compound with the King. His pledges are Roger Earl Bigod‚ Gaffridus de Say, and William de Warenna ; and the Sheriff is thereupon commanded to let him have his lands again. Tournaments had been strictly prohibited by three general Couocils, but Richard found it convenient and practicable to raise money by granting dispensatione for violating the precepts of the Church :- one of the numerous proofs that the autho- rity of the Clergy went for nothing, when· ever the governing powers chose to com- bine with the multitude in setting their doctrines at defiance.
